ColtExpress ScoreHeuristic 2021

The results in the tabs below show the MCTS parameters optimised for ColtExpress when using a ScoreHeuristic instead of the default one. The opponents (OSLA and MCTS; not RND) also use the ScoreHeuristic, so should improve in quality as well.

Conclusions:

  • Tuning MCTS (and doubling the budget) gives only a small advance over the baseline MCTS (58% in 2P, 39% in 3P, 30% in 4P). But performance is much better against the RND and OSLA agents (97%+ versus 31%-77% previously)
  • In general the signal from NTBEA optimisation is much stronger, with fewer flat marginal distributions across parameters.
  • MultiNTBEA still gives pretty dreadful results - but does seem to detect that using MAST for rollouts is a poor option (it makes these much more time-consuming)
  • The universally important parameters are rolloutLength (as before, it needs to be 30+), selectionPolicy (SIMPLE, not ROBUST), rolloutType (Random >> MAST). maxTreeDepth is not important.
  • The opponentTreePolicy is more important (unexpectedly) for OSLA, RND opponents, with Self and MultiTree options dogin well.
  • The treePolicy is important against an MCTS opponent, with UCB-tuned doing especially well.
